===Noun===
{{en-noun-unc}}
{{wikipedia}}

# A light, silvery metal extracted from [[bauxite]], and a chemical element (''symbol'' Al) with an [[atomic number]] of 13.

====Alternative spellings====
*[[aluminum]] (''US'') (''see also'' '''Usage notes''' ''below'')

====Usage notes====
#Both spellings are used in Canada.
#For information on the origins of the two spellings, see [[w:Aluminium#Spelling|the Wikipedia article]]

====Synonyms====
*[[alumium]] (''obsolete'')
*[[E173]] when used as a [[food colouring]]

